pr_review_body:
This looks great. A few suggestions for consideration:

1. Feels like we should add a test here since we're relying on CLI output (and this has changed in the past). Perhaps we can add a check in just one of our tests in this block: https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/blob/master/sdk/go/x/auto/local_workspace_test.go#L166-L174. Given that the structure of the URL could change based on the PULUMI_TEST_ORG, maybe we can just check if it starts with `app.pulumi.com` or something? 
2. It would be great to add this to our primary `Stack.Up` example as I think this is super useful functionality to highlight for users: https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/blob/master/sdk/go/x/auto/example_test.go#L921
3. I like having this generic function that accepts just a string. This means that users can combine this method with streaming output, or output from any command. What do you think about adding a utility method on `UpResult` to make this a little easier to discover for the common case? https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/blob/master/sdk/go/x/auto/stack.go#L585-L593

```go
func (ur *UpdateResult) GetPermalink() (string, error) {
 return GetPermalink(ur.Stdout)
}
```

Lots of changes. So, this is a major refactoring job addressing 2 issues; #974 and ? (refactoring task of putting http execution at one place).
Probably it would be a good idea to change the title;
`Add {set,get}_bucket_versioning() APIs`

@P403n1x87 Checking my understanding: you've basically changed things such that ddtracepy does not proactively import any of the modules for which there are integrations in contrib. If that's correct, I'm on board with this change. I left a bunch of clarifying comments and suggestions. 

I think it would be helpful for reviewers' understanding and our future selves if you also filled out the description's "Proposed Workflow" section.

Please let me know if anything's unclear and when you'd like another review.

@nfelt PTAL and see if this aligns with what you were thinking of.

@psybuzz do note that after index.html, our header appeared a bit different :\ I could not discern exactly what has caused the regression so I had to apply flex.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2547313/101855531-671ade00-3b18-11eb-97ef-206ab3bee362.png)

Thanks again for taking time to contribute to LightGBM!

I left some small suggestions. Please also fix the linting errors listed in https://travis-ci.org/github/microsoft/LightGBM/jobs/746519935. You can reproduce these errors locally by running `Rscript .ci/lint_r_code.R $(pwd)`.

@zenggyu one other question...are you interested in completely finishing #3390 ? I originally set it up file-by-file like that for Hacktoberfest, but now that Hacktoberfest is over I'd like to finish it. If you have the time and interest, I'd be grateful if you'd handle the rest of the files there in one or two additional pull requests after this one (doesn't have to be one-fiile-per-PR).

@codewithnick Thanks for your efforts 💯 
Please take a look at my comments 🔥 

You should rebase your `dev` branch. It's out of date and lead to some conflicts

